underlying_goal: The user wanted to verify and complete the implementation of a coding challenge problem (In-Memory Database), ensuring it passed all tests and met all specifications.
primary_success: Identified and fixed two non-obvious bugs in the implementation: an incorrect TTL expiry check (`<` vs `<=`) and flawed logic in the `restore` function's timestamp lookup.
brief_summary: The user asked Claude to test an implementation for a coding problem. Claude ran existing tests, then performed a deeper verification against JSON test cases, uncovering and fixing two bugs related to TTL expiry and historical data restoration. After fixing the bugs, Claude confirmed all tests passed and the implementation was fully spec-compliant.
